Cetan- Sparrow hawk:  You know, akita mani yo, to observe and listen as you walk.  That is what kept you and a lot of good grunts alive.  Since you have made the walk, let the young men observe and listen to you as you &quot;talk.&quot; your voice is a strong clear one.<br>
Chet- Having PTSD means that you are a healthy human responding to that which was far outside the realm of normal human experience.  My skin crawls when I hear it put into words, so eloquently, by Bro. Cook, &quot;Cetan.&quot;  It is not what you did with your hands and feet in Viet Nam that counts the most, it is what you did with your heart and spirit then and now.  I gave you a name on another thread.  My forefathers called wagons rolling wood and guns were called magic iron.<br>
I have a better name for you and all our brothers, it is &quot;Cante Tinza,&quot; and it means brave heart.  To the greatest warriors and to the young boys who held the spare horses, we say the same, &quot;Hunhunhe pange`ca,&quot; outstanding performance.<br>
I offer you Catka, my left hand, which is closest to my heart.
